 authorial voice as fleshy combinings of meaning and music.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aIntonation (Phonetics). 0aOral communicationxPhilosophy. 0aTranslating and interpretingxPhilosophy. 0aVoice in literature. 4aMusic. 4aPhilosophy & Theory. 4aReligion. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Mind & Body.2bisacsh  aflesh.  amusicality.  aspeaking voice.  aspoken word.  avoice.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311072902340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823270026zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823270026423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823270026/original  a978-3-11-072902-3  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK